    <h3>MWI Animal Health — Territory Sales Manager</h3>
    <p class="job-meta">October 2021 – March 2026 &middot; 4 years 6 months</p>
    <p>Directed a $9.2 million healthcare territory supporting approximately 160 veterinary hospitals across Central and Northeast Florida. Partnered with veterinarians, practice owners, practice managers, specialists, and veterinary technicians to improve patient care, operational efficiency, and business performance through laboratory diagnostics, point-of-care diagnostics, healthcare technology, pharmaceuticals, vaccines, medical supplies, and capital equipment.</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Managed one of the company's largest Florida territories while achieving 101.9% of annual sales objective</li>
      <li>Served as a trusted business advisor to veterinary practices by delivering integrated solutions spanning diagnostics, healthcare technology, pharmaceuticals, vaccines, medical supplies, and capital equipment</li>
      <li>Consulted with veterinary practices on workflow optimization, inventory management, practice growth, and equipment planning</li>
      <li>Developed comprehensive capital equipment proposals for new veterinary hospital startups, including dental systems, anesthesia equipment, surgical lasers, IV pumps, cage banks, and diagnostic equipment</li>
      <li>Demonstrated and implemented AllyDVM, Replenitrac, and Furscription software solutions to improve client communication, patient compliance, inventory management, and practice efficiency</li>
      <li>Recovered a major competitive account by rebuilding the customer relationship over approximately one year, resulting in a renewed long-term purchasing agreement</li>
      <li>Retained one of the territory's largest emergency veterinary organizations with four hospital locations through proactive relationship management</li>
      <li>Utilized Salesforce CRM to manage forecasting, opportunity development, pipeline management, and strategic territory planning</li>
    </ul>

